HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1027
By Littleton
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the local emergency
management agencies of Tennessee for their
meritorious service.
WHEREAS, the safety, resilience, and well-being of Tennesseans depend in large
measure on the continuous efforts of local emergency management agencies, whose personnel
stand prepared to protect life and property in times of crisis; and
WHEREAS, local emergency management agencies provide essential "blue-sky"
capabilities and day-to-day readiness functions that strengthen communities, including hazard
identification, risk reduction planning, training, exercises, public outreach, and collaboration with
local officials, schools, healthcare facilities, and volunteer and faith-based partners; and
WHEREAS, these agencies lead and support preparedness activities that help
communities anticipate and withstand emergencies and disasters, including the development
and maintenance of emergency operations plans, the coordination of resources, and the
promotion of individual and community preparedness; and
WHEREAS, during disasters and emergencies, local emergency management agencies
coordinate response operations, support incident management, maintain situational awareness,
facilitate communication among local, regional, state, and federal partners, and help deliver
timely information to the public; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee communities have faced significant emergencies and disasters
in recent years, to name only a handful among many, the Waverly floods, the 2020 tornadoes,
the Gatlinburg wildfires, Tropical Storm Helene, and the January 2026 winter storm, and local
emergency management personnel have consistently met these challenges with skill, courage,
and determination; and
HJR1027
013742
- 1 -

WHEREAS, following emergencies, local emergency management agencies play a
critical role in recovery by assessing impacts, documenting damages, coordinating debris
management and unmet needs, supporting disaster assistance programs, and helping
communities rebuild stronger and more resilient than before; and
WHEREAS, the personnel of local emergency management agencies demonstrate
professionalism, dedication, and selfless commitment, often working long hours under stressful
conditions, to ensure Tennessee communities are prepared for, respond to, and recover from
emergencies of all kinds; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the men and women, both past and present, of
the local emergency management agencies of Tennessee for their meritorious service,
extending our deepest appreciation for their dedication and commitment to a job well done.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
